basicQuestions.answerText:
Treatment of Wolfram syndrome is supportive and based on the signs and symptoms present in each person. For example, almost all affected people require insulin to treat <a href="http://www.nlm.nih.gov/medlineplus/ency/article/000305.htm" target="_blank">diabetes mellitus</a>. People with hearing loss may benefit from hearing aids or <a href="http://www.nlm.nih.gov/medlineplus/ency/article/007203.htm" target="_blank">cochlear implantation</a>.[7125][7970][7971] <br />
<br />
For more detailed information please visit the GeneReviews section regarding the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK4144/#wfs.Management" target="_blank">treatment and management of Wolfram syndrome</a>.&nbsp;
